#: ../../manual/render/lighting/lamps/area.rst:4
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "面光"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/lamps/area.rst:6
msgid ""
"The *Area* lamp simulates light originating from a surface (or surface-"
"like) emitter. For example, a TV screen, office neon lamps, a window, or "
"a cloudy sky are just a few types of area lamp. The area lamp produces "
"shadows with soft borders by sampling a lamp along a grid the size of "
"which is defined by the user. This is in direct contrast to point-like "
"artificial lights which produce sharp borders."
msgstr ""
"*Area（区域/面光）* 灯模拟来自表面（或类似表面）发射的光。例如，电视屏"
"幕、办公室霓虹灯、窗户或多云的天空只是几种类型的区域灯。区域灯通过沿用户"
"定义的网格对灯进行采样，产生具有软边界的阴影。这与点状的人造光形成了直接"
"的对比，后者产生了尖锐的边界。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/lamps/area.rst:14
msgid "Lamp Options"
msgstr "灯光选项"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/lamps/area.rst:23
msgid "Distance, Energy and Color"
msgstr "距离、能量和颜色"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/lamps/area.rst:17
msgid ""
"These settings are common to most types of lamps, and are described in :"
"doc:`Light Properties </render/lighting/lights/lamp_panel>`."
msgstr ""
"这些设置对大多数类型的灯都是通用的，说明在 :doc:`Light Properties </"
"render/lighting/lights/lamp_panel>` 。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/lamps/area.rst:20
msgid ""
"Note that the *Distance* setting is much more sensitive and important "
"for *Area* lamps than for others; usually any objects within the range "
"of *Distance* will be blown out and overexposed. For best results, set "
"the *Distance* to just below the distance to the object that you want to "
"illuminate."
msgstr ""
"注意，*距离* 设置对 *区域* 灯比其他灯更为敏感和重要；通常，*距离* 范围内"
"的任何物体都会曝光过度。为获得最佳效果，请将 *距离* 设置为刚好低于要照亮"
"的问题的距离。"

